{"TopicId":176379,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Ability to trim your planes","CreatedByName":"TrueKerbalnaut","CreatedById":189332,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-03T21:12:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"TrueKerbalnaut","CreatedById":189332,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-03T21:12:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk this is somthing i think is \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIMPORTANT\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E for KSP, being able to trim you planes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you ever made and airplane and started flying it around the world (or just a long distance) and had the plane slowly start pitching downwards? If u just left the controls alone you would eventually crash right.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell this is why i want \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAIRPLANE TRIMMING\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E \u003Cu\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#2ecc71;\u0022\u003Eplease help me notify squad and get this to be a feature ingame\u003C/span\u003E \u003C/u\u003Ebecause its so frustrating doing long straight flights on kerbin. So please help me notify squad about this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want more info on what trimming is just read this little bit of info its fairly simple: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://aviation.stackexchange.com/questions/164/what-does-the-term-trimming-most-commonly-mean-in-aviation\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://aviation.stackexchange.com/questions/164/what-does-the-term-trimming-most-commonly-mean-in-aviation\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can also find videos on yt on how trimming works and its uses!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ETo squad\u003C/strong\u003E: please add this its much needed. You could make it like and optional clickable button when u right click on a probe or a cockpit but man would this be useful. Besides real airplanes use this in pretty much every airplane today so why not add it in ksp?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SnailsAttack","CreatedById":184399,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-03T21:59:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t KSP already have trimming?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-03T23:58:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223409752\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176379\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221530655165\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184399\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SnailsAttack\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, SnailsAttack said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t KSP already have trimming?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"guesswho2778","CreatedById":170733,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-04T00:17:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlt \u002B w/a/s/d \u003Cs\u003Enote you cant see how far you trimming them though\u003C/s\u003E im an idiot nvm\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh and turn off \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E if you want to use it\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-07-13T06:52:17Z\u0022 title=\u002207/13/2018 06:52  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 13, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by guesswho2778\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TrueKerbalnaut","CreatedById":189332,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-04T02:49:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLol im such noob xD. Thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-04T05:50:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think \u003Cstrong\u003EAlt \u002B X\u003C/strong\u003E resets all the trims to 0%.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blaarkies","CreatedById":153700,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-04T07:21:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223409816\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176379\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221530663466\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022170733\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022guesswho2778\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, guesswho2778 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlt \u002B w/a/s/d note you cant see how far you trimming them though\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh and turn off \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E if you want to use it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLook at the input dials in the bottom left of the screen. If you do not touch the controls, and have \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E off, those dials will show the current amount of trim\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blaarkies","CreatedById":153700,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-05T16:23:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1531656718\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/164522-144-122-trim-indicator-v1440-%E2%80%94-2018-06-25/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:224px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lego_Prodigy","CreatedById":187421,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-05T16:42:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you play stock, theres always gonna be something that is odd in your plane\u0027s flying characteristics. Just don\u0027t let go of the controls, as thats a very bad habit to pick up in flying games.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}